headline: Nike earnings, Fed meeting, Nov. PCE: What to Watch Next Week
summary: Market Domination Overtime Hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton detail the top market headlines to watch for next week. All eyes are on the Federal Reserve as the Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) prepares for its December 17-18 meeting. Wall Street is closely monitoring the central bank's upcoming interest rate decision, with markets currently pricing in an expected 25 basis point cut. A slew of earnings reports are scheduled for release, featuring companies including Nike (NKE), Micron (MU), General Mills (GIS), Lennar (LEN), FedEx (FDX), and Accenture (ACN). On the economic calendar, two key releases are due: November's Personal Consumption Expenditures (PCE) index— the Fed's preferred measure of inflation —will be released on Friday, while Retail Sales data will be published earlier in the week. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Angel Smith
